* Class 14 [2019-03-04 Mon]
** 2D NMR refers to having 2 dimensions like a carbon dimension and a proton dimension
** This greatly improves identification capacity
** COSY is Hydrogen-Hydrogen 2D (?)
** Transformations:
*** Fourier transform
*** Baseline correction
*** Phase correction
** Chromatogram peak area lets you quantify concentration
** Generally speaking, decoupling is applied to carbon spectra
** Need an internal standard to get absolute concentrations



